schedule:
第1週: Class begins;
第2週: Preview of electrical systems; 
第3週: Preview of experiments: Motor and Drive Diagnosis
第4週: Influences of sensor positions in motor detection;
第5週: Relationship between unbalance and vibration in motor;
第6週: Effects of lubrication to stability of motor running; Effects of loadings to motor running;
第7週: Dynamic balance, loosening, and axial bending of motor;
第8週: Measuring temperature of motor in operation.
第9週:  Midterm examination
第10週: Basics Principles for Electric Machine Analysis; Direct-Current Machines; Experiments: Reference-Frame Theory;
第11週: Symmetrical Induction Machines; Synchronous Machines; Theory of Brushless dc Machines;
第12週: Machine Equations in Operational Impedances and Time Constants; Linearized Machine Equations; Reduced-Order Machine Equations;
第13週: Symmetrical and Unsymmetrical 2-Phase Induction Machines; Semi-controlled Bridge Converters; Dc Machine Drives;
第14週: Fully Controlled 3-Phase Bridge Converters; Induction Motor Drives; Brushless dc Motor Drives;
第15週: Presentations of group I;
第16週: Presentations of group II;
第17週:. Presentations of group III;
第18週: Final examination

scorePolicy:
1. Assignments &amp; reports;
